08:44.958 --> 08:48.829
Renaldo Jr.
We called him Wren.

08:48.862 --> 08:52.800
He worked for Benjamin J.
Bateman, A.K.A. Benny.

08:52.833 --> 08:56.604
Benny had absolutely no moral
convictions on how he made money.

08:56.637 --> 09:00.941
More than prostitution, extortion or
drugs... which he was definitely into...

09:00.974 --> 09:03.152
His main commodity was
contributing to the delinquency...

09:03.176 --> 09:06.213
of every kid
in the neighborhood.

09:06.246 --> 09:09.983
What the fuck is wrong with you? This is
attention that we don't fuckin' need, man.

09:10.017 --> 09:12.252
They started it, Wren.
Yo, you shut the fuck up.

09:19.059 --> 09:23.096
- How old are you, man?
- Fourteen.

09:23.130 --> 09:27.601
You and your little team, y'all got
some heart, man. Don't lose that, man.

09:29.069 --> 09:31.972
- Get outta here.
- Hell, no, man. They owe us money.

09:32.005 --> 09:35.308
Fuck you, bitch. Come on, man.
Yo. Yo. Train?

09:35.342 --> 09:38.011
Do that again, man,
I'm gonna fuck you up myself, man.

09:38.045 --> 09:40.080
How much money
they owe you, little man?

09:40.113 --> 09:43.216
Twenty dollars.
Where's your money at, Lathan?

09:43.250 --> 09:45.653
I ain't got no money, Wren.
Come here, man.

09:45.686 --> 09:47.621
What the fuck, man?
Hold on there.

09:51.925 --> 09:54.303
- That's gonna have to do it.
- What the fuck, Wren? Give me back...

09:54.327 --> 09:56.730
Shut up, man.
That's gonna have to do you, man.

09:56.764 --> 09:59.667
- What are we supposed to do with this?
- Smoke it. Sniff it.

09:59.700 --> 10:02.836
Do whatever, man.
It's more than the $20.

10:02.870 --> 10:04.805
Hey, yo, Tristan,
I swear to God, dawg.

10:04.838 --> 10:07.074
Give me my shit back right now.

10:07.107 --> 10:09.309
