Man, I don't know.

17:02.722 --> 17:06.126
Damn! We gonna get higher
than a motherfucker!

17:06.159 --> 17:08.060
Hell, yeah!

17:09.529 --> 17:11.531
What you trippin' on, Tris?

17:14.201 --> 17:16.636
What if we didn't
smoke all of it?

17:16.669 --> 17:19.106
I know you ain't talkin'
about sellin' it.

17:19.138 --> 17:22.275
Why not?
But where, man?

17:22.309 --> 17:25.145
Lathan and them got it locked down
from Gold Fall to Four Corners.

17:25.178 --> 17:28.448
In case y'all don't remember, that was
Benny up in that Cadillac this afternoon.

17:28.481 --> 17:31.151
And I ain't tryin'
to fuck with Benny, man.

17:31.184 --> 17:33.486
Who said anything about
sellin' it on the streets?

17:33.520 --> 17:35.788
We can sell it at school.

17:35.822 --> 17:39.726
All you got is a few burnouts
selling nickel bags to they friends.

17:39.759 --> 17:41.828
We'd be the only crew.

17:41.861 --> 17:44.364
We could supply the burnouts
and take they customers.

17:46.433 --> 17:50.237
And that ain't even the beautiful thing.
What's the beautiful thing?

17:50.270 --> 17:53.506
We don't have to worry
about gettin' caught...

17:53.540 --> 17:55.775
'cause we gonna be
supplyin' the teachers.

17:55.808 --> 17:57.877
Ain't no teachers gonna
buy no herb, Tris.

17:57.910 --> 18:01.114
Shit, man. We just saw
Mr. Thomas buy from Sam today.

18:01.148 --> 18:04.384
Damn motherfuckin'
skippy. Shit.

18:04.417 --> 18:06.686
I'm with you, Tris.
E.

18:06.719 --> 18:09.389
Me too.
Let's do it.

18:09.422 --> 18:12.559
Let's do this.
Let's go.

18:15.362 --> 18:18.265
When we ran out of the stash
we ripped off from Sam,

18:18.298 --> 18:20.433
we started buying from him
to supply our customers.

18:20.467 --> 18:24.504
Pee Wee squared it with Sam
about us stealin' from him,

18:24.537 --> 18:26.906
so we let him get high
as much as he wants.

18:26.939 --> 18:29.642
We were buying so much shit,
it didn't matter to us.

18:32.412 --> 18:34.881
At first, we thought
the money was pretty good,

18:34.914 --> 18:37.217
but we had to kick
so much of it back to Sam...

18:37.250 --> 18:40.920
that we realized
he was the one gettin' paid.

18:40.953 --> 18:43.523
That's when I decided
to grow our own shit,

18:43.556 --> 18:46.693
and then the paper
came in nonstop.

18:46.726 --> 18:49.329
E-Bone got pretty good
at growin' that shit too.

18:49.362 --> 18:52.232
Twinkie helped us out by
lettin' us use the back room...

18:52.265 --> 18:54.634
in one of his girls' apartments.

18:54.667 --> 18:57.304
We kicked back a couple hundred
to her every once in a while...

18:57.337 --> 18:59.806
for lettin' us keep the place.

18:59.839 --> 19:03.743
She appreciated that
and let us know.

19:03.776 --> 19:05.612
We couldn't believe
the life we were livin'.

19:10.283 --> 19:12.652
Where you goin' E-Bone?
Where you goin', boy?

19:12.685 --> 19:14.821
That's some dope new gear
you sportin', E-Bone.

19:18.391 --> 19:20.427
- Get up, girl.
- What the fuck y'all want?

19:20.460 --> 19:22.895
You ain't so tough without your
crew, you little punk?

19:22.929 --> 19:25.698
I told Tristan I was comin'
back for my shit, didn't I?

19:25.732 --> 19:28.132
I guess I'm just gonna have to
take it out your ass, ain't I?

19:40.847 --> 19:43.250
We bombin' on all you
punk-ass bitches!

19:43.283 --> 19:44.917
This is our motherfuckin' block!

19:57.597 --> 20:00.500
Hey, Uncle Rob.

20:00.533 --> 20:03.603
Hey, little Mack.
How you doin'?

20:03.636 --> 20:06.506
Good. Pretty good.
Hey. The place...

20:06.539 --> 20:08.908
The place looks good.

20:08.941 --> 20:11.511
What this place
looks like is empty.

20:11.544 --> 20:13.513
It ain't caught on the
way I thought it would.

20:18.485 --> 20:21.254
Boy, what are you doin'?

20:21.288 --> 20:23.290
It's the first of the month.

20:23.323 --> 20:25.992
Look, the rent on this place
ain't gonna pay itself.

20:26.025 --> 20:28.395
The money don't know where it comes
from, so just take it.

20:28.428 --> 20:31.798
Boy, if your daddy knew what you was
doin', he'd kill you.

20:31.831 --> 20:35.435
And if he knew I was taking money from you
to run this place, I'd be just as dead.

20:35.468 --> 20:37.670
But he doesn't know, and,
as long as he lives,

20:37.704 --> 20:40.840
he doesn't ever need
to know about this, right?

20:45.011 --> 20:47.947
Right.
The barbershop's gonna pick up.

20:47.980 --> 20:52.685
I know it will. I mean,
I believe in you, Uncle Rob.

20:52.719 --> 20:55.000
What good is makin' money if
you can't do nothin' with it?

20:57.890 --> 21:00.793
You know, boy, sometimes I think
you the grown-up and I'm the child.

21:00.827 --> 21:04.531
Now, we gotta get on home
before Mama's dinner gets cold.

21:06.466 --> 21:08.635
Hey, Tristan, hold up.
There's somethin'...

21:08.668 --> 21:10.970
I been wantin' to talk to you
about for a long while now.

21:11.003 --> 21:13.340
I really gotta go, Uncle...
Don't you interrupt me.

21:13.373 --> 21:16.543
Now, if you gonna
be in this game...

21:16.576 --> 21:19.788
And from the looks of things, it looks like
you done made up your mind about that...

21:19.812 --> 21:23.383
You got to realize
that this is a losin' game.

21:23.416 --> 21:26.886
Drug dealers don't have pensions,
they don't end up with retirement funds...

21:26.919 --> 21:29.088
and they don't end up with
the big house on the hill.

21:29.121 --> 21:32.659
They end up dead or
wishin' that they were.

21:32.692 --> 21:36.429
So, what's your point, Unc?
Make a plan. That's the point.

21:36.463 --> 21:39.466
Do somethin' with your money.

21:39.499 --> 21:42.902
Set yourself up to get out of
this game when the time is right.

21:42.935 --> 21:45.037
I'm talkin' about investments...

21:45.071 --> 21:47.374
Legitimate investments.

21:47.407 --> 21:49.576
Now, I'm gonna take this
money as an investment.

21:49.609 --> 21:53.012
You investin' in my barbershop.

21:53.045 --> 21:56.383
I'm gonna teach you the ins
and outs of this business.

21:56.416 --> 21:59.786
From now on, we not just
relatives, we are partners.

21:59.819 --> 22:02.355
And we gonna make this
a success together.

22:04.391 --> 22:06.092
Partners.
Partners.

22:09.496 --> 22:12.632
All right. You tell your mama
I'm gonna be a little late.

22:12.665 --> 22:14.501
All right.
Y'all go on and eat without me.

22:14.534 --> 22:16.903
All right.

22:16.936 --> 22:20.039
Baby, you haven't eaten
your mashed potatoes.

22:20.072 --> 22:22.141
I don't like them.

22:22.174 --> 22:24.544
But they'll make you
big and strong.

22:24.577 --> 22:26.946
You've been saying that
for years, Mom.

22:26.979 --> 22:29.749
What do you know about
"years," little girl?

22:29.782 --> 22:32.519
You only eight.
Yeah, but I'm an old soul.

22:34.987 --> 22:37.590
"Old soul."

22:37.624 --> 22:38.991
How's everything
with you, Tristan?

22:39.025 --> 22:41.628
Good, Pops.
Honey?

22:41.661 --> 22:45.465
Have you told Tristan
you saw his report card?

22:45.498 --> 22:49.469
No, I didn't.
Straight A's again?

22:49.502 --> 22:52.539
You keep this up, we gonna
have to send you to Harvard.

22:52.572 --> 22:55.107
- I'll get it.
- I'll get it. You help your mother.

22:58.778 --> 23:01.448
Tristan.
Simon and Marlon are here.

23:03.950 --> 23:07.053
Wass... Wassup, man? What y'all doin' here?
You... You want some chicken?

23:09.656 --> 23:13.059
- We got a problem, man.
- What's up?

23:13.092 --> 23:15.628
It's E-Bone.

23:26.706 --> 23:30.843
Tristan, Simon, Money.
Broke-ass Pee Wee.

23:30.877 --> 23:32.912
Someone try to break
your legs too?

23:32.945 --> 23:35.047
Took you guys long enough to get here.
Shut your ass.

23:35.081 --> 23:37.450
Can we see him?

23:37.484 --> 23:39.486
Come on in.

23:47.560 --> 23:49.962
- Hey. What up, fellas?
- What up, E?

23:49.996 --> 23:52.899
What's the deal, E?
How you feelin', killer?

23:52.932 --> 23:56.068
Come on, now.
Edward, I want you to finish this.

23:56.102 --> 23:59.572
Look, Nana, I need
to talk to my friends.

23:59.606 --> 24:02.709
I'm not going anywhere
until you finish eating.

24:02.742 --> 24:05.211
It's okay, Mrs. Winslett.
I'll make sure he eats it.

24:05.244 --> 24:08.715
I'll make sure he eats it all.

24:08.748 --> 24:11.584
- Is that all right with you, Edward?
- Yes, Nana.

24:11.618 --> 24:14.020
I'll be outside if you need me.

24:14.053 --> 24:16.623
Okay.

24:22.995 --> 24:25.932
Make sure he eats
all of it, Tristan.

24:25.965 --> 24:28.735
Yeah. Make sure he
gets it and not Simon.

24:33.205 --> 24:36.943
I ain't gonna feed ya.

24:36.976 --> 24:40.547
- So, do you feel as bad as you look?
- What took y'all so long?

24:40.580 --> 24:42.549
Yo, it was Lathan and them,
wasn't it?

24:42.582 --> 24:44.984
- Yeah.
- Yo, it don't make sense, E...

24:45.017 --> 24:47.754
Him fucking you up like this
over a couple of ounces?

24:47.787 --> 24:51.558
Three months ago?
It ain't makin' sense, E.

24:51.591 --> 24:53.626
Hey, what you
talkin' about, man?

24:53.660 --> 24:57.764
We straight embarrassed him,
in front of Benny too.

24:57.797 --> 25:00.232
I say you got lucky, E.

25:00.266 --> 25:02.802
He might have killed your ass.

25:02.835 --> 25:06.038
- Look, what happened, E-Bone?
- What you mean, "What happened?"

25:06.072 --> 25:08.007
I got fucked up.
That's what happened.

25:09.108 --> 25:11.544
Look, Money's right.

25:11.578 --> 25:14.089
Lathan wouldn't have came after
you like this over a couple ounces.

25:14.113 --> 25:16.115
- Yeah. Come on, E.
- Too much time has passed.

25:16.148 --> 25:18.885
So, what happened?

25:18.918 --> 25:21.287
Look, I was doin' business
on the street.

25:21.320 --> 25:23.322
You bullshittin'.

25:23.355 --> 25:27.059
- We said only at school.
- Man, I know what we said.

25:27.093 --> 25:28.937
But there's money on the street, kid.
I'm telling you.

25:28.961 --> 25:32.732
So, in other words, you almost
get killed for a few pennies.

25:32.765 --> 25:35.835
Man, is you stupid?
Pennies?

25:35.868 --> 25:38.270
Money, go over there and
bring me that jar of peanuts.

25:45.244 --> 25:47.246
Shit.

25:52.284 --> 25:54.286
Man, let me help you.

26:01.160 --> 26:05.998
Yeah, and this is only from
me working just three weeks.

26:06.032 --> 26:09.602
Man, imagine all of us working,
man, for months or even years.

26:09.636 --> 26:12.304
Just think of all the shit
we can get, Tris.

26:12.338 --> 26:15.174
Yo, what about Lathan?
We still gotta deal with him.

26:15.207 --> 26:17.677
Man, fuck Lathan, man.

26:19.712 --> 26:21.748
Look.

26:21.781 --> 26:23.983
Hey, where the fuck
you get that, man?

26:24.016 --> 26:27.820
Dennis and his brother Randy robbed a
gun store in Brockton a couple days ago.

26:27.854 --> 26:31.924
They got all kinds of steel.
We can get anything we want.

26:34.160 --> 26:35.762
Let's go, fellas.

26:39.231 --> 26:41.233
Get better, man.

26:43.135 --> 26:45.404
Hey, I want y'all
to know somethin'.

26:45.437 --> 26:48.174
I wasn't holdin' out on y'all.
I was gonna tell you.

26:50.309 --> 26:53.946
I just wanted to see what was out
there on the street, you know?

26:56.315 --> 26:58.885
Yeah, man. Yeah, man. We know.

26:58.918 --> 27:00.953
Get better.
Take care of that eye.

27:00.987 --> 27:02.889
Holler at you in a minute.

27:21.874 --> 27:24.711
- Hi, Tristan.
- Hey, wassup?

27:27.246 --> 27:30.082
Shit. You're not gonna speak?

27:30.116 --> 27:33.252
You talkin' to me?
I ain't talkin' to myself.

27:33.285 --> 27:36.355
I don't think I remember your name.
You gonna do me like that.

27:36.388 --> 27:40.827
You're cute and everything, and I know
you got this little mack thing goin' on,

27:40.860 --> 27:42.895
but I can't be messin'
with no drug dealers.

27:42.929 --> 27:45.231
I ain't no drug dealer.
Come on, Tristan. I'm not stupid.

27:45.264 --> 27:47.767
So you do remember my name.

27:47.800 --> 27:51.938
Okay, so maybe I do, but that
doesn't change the fact that you're...

27:54.140 --> 27:56.042
What's that?
Open it.

28:00.747 --> 28:03.449
It's beautiful.
It's yours.

28:03.482 --> 28:09.188
I can't take this. You have to.
It's nonrefundable.

28:09.221 --> 28:14.193
Listen, I hear you on this little drug-dealing
thing you're talkin' about, right?

28:14.226 --> 28:17.396
But I ain't no dealer. I just help
out my friends from time to time.

28:17.429 --> 28:20.299
That's all? That's all.
I promise.

28:22.101 --> 28:24.136
Thanks for the necklace.

28:24.170 --> 28:26.272
So can I walk you home?

28:26.305 --> 28:30.076
Okay.
You look beautiful with that.

28:30.109 --> 28:33.345
- You sure they in there?
- That's the word.

28:33.379 --> 28:36.315
Let's do this.

28:36.348 --> 28:40.486
I wasn't content with what
we had just dealin' at school.

28:41.988 --> 28:45.491
E-Bone kicked off
the inevitable.

28:45.524 --> 28:49.328
First rule of business...
Control the market.

28:49.361 --> 28:52.899
It was time to elevate the game.

28:52.932 --> 28:55.201
Shit. How many books
y'all get?

28:55.234 --> 28:58.237
Y'all count 'em up.
I gotta take a piss.

28:59.505 --> 29:01.808
Lathan be cheatin'.
When he comes back,

29:01.841 --> 29:03.943
I'm gonna put
a bullet in his ass.

29:03.976 --> 29:06.946
That's why I don't like playin' with
him, 'cause he always be cheatin'.

29:06.979 --> 29:08.480
♪♪

29:33.039 --> 29:37.143
Aw, shit! What the fuck
you goin' to do, bitch?

29:37.176 --> 29:40.179
Little Tristan?

29:40.212 --> 29:43.082
You better kill my ass
right now, motherfucker,

29:43.115 --> 29:45.351
if you got the balls, bitch.

29:48.187 --> 29:51.357
Mother...

29:51.390 --> 29:54.193
I read this book about
World War II one time.

29:54.226 --> 29:56.371
Damn. One of the soldiers said
that every time he killed someone,

29:56.395 --> 29:59.565
he saw the face
of the first man he murdered.

29:59.598 --> 30:02.101
It's like none of
the other faces register.

30:02.134 --> 30:04.837
You kept killin' the same guy
over and over again. Mama.

30:10.009 --> 30:12.078
Lathan was the first cat
I ever killed.

30:12.111 --> 30:14.613
The soldier was right.

30:14.646 --> 30:17.449
I killed other dudes,

30:17.483 --> 30:20.552
but, to this day,
I can only see Lathan's face,

30:20.586 --> 30:23.890
knowin'... Come on, Tris.
Let's go, man.

30:23.923 --> 30:25.958
Knowin' he was gonna die.

30:25.992 --> 30:29.228
Come on, man. Let's go.
In less than a second,

30:29.261 --> 30:31.864
what little bit of childhood
we had left was gone.

30:31.898 --> 30:35.134
I had made decisions about my life
based on my friendships with my boys,

30:35.167 --> 30:38.370
but, until that moment,
I could always walk away.

30:38.404 --> 30:41.540
Now there was no walkin' away.
Lathan!

30:41.573 --> 30:45.444
I was no longer a kid.
Now I was a gangster.

30:45.477 --> 30:49.015
We all were, and that's
the way we wanted it.

30:49.048 --> 30:51.083
Weed is
a pretty lightweight drug,

30:51.117 --> 30:53.352
even back then.

30:53.385 --> 30:57.656
In that game, you usually ain't got to
worry about no one tryin' to murder you.

30:57.689 --> 31:00.927
I killed Lathan because
he was becomin' a pain,

31:00.960 --> 31:04.030
and I knew I would feel
better once he was gone.

31:04.063 --> 31:07.934
Now everyone had no choice
but to take us seriously.

31:07.967 --> 31:10.269
But I had to keep
telling myself over and over,

31:10.302 --> 31:13.039
it was just business.

31:13.072 --> 31:16.342
I said it enough times that I
actually started to believe it.

31:16.375 --> 31:18.510
There wasn't any reason
to kill the rest of 'em.

31:18.544 --> 31:21.613
Without Lathan,
they were nothin'.

31:21.647 --> 31:24.450
And no one goes to the cops
in this neighborhood.

31:28.154 --> 31:30.389
Things were different now.

31:30.422 --> 31:33.125
We were ghetto superstars
before, but,

31:33.159 --> 31:36.228
after we took out Lathan
and took over all his customers,

31:37.329 --> 31:39.498
now we were ghetto legends.

31:44.436 --> 31:46.638
But there was one face...

31:46.672 --> 31:49.241
that didn't show a look
of admiration or respect.

32:18.270 --> 32:23.275
♪ These are the days of our
lives that we're livin' ♪

32:23.309 --> 32:28.981
♪ We're livin' the days of our deadliest
sins ♪ You motherfuckers sit down.

32:29.015 --> 32:30.682
♪♪ You know why you're here?

32:30.716 --> 32:32.751
No.

32:32.784 --> 32:36.488
- You know who I am though?
- Yeah, we know.

32:45.231 --> 32:48.334
- What's that?
- It's new business.

32:48.367 --> 32:50.669
It's your new business.

32:50.702 --> 32:53.139
We doin' pretty good
with the one we got.

32:53.172 --> 32:56.042
Boy, you ain't doin' shit.

32:56.075 --> 33:00.212
You take your best day
and you times it by 10,

33:00.246 --> 33:04.216
and it's your worst day ever
selling this shit right here.

33:04.250 --> 33:06.285
Word?
You like that?

33:06.318 --> 33:09.488
You like the sound of that?

33:09.521 --> 33:11.657
Well, if it's so good,
why you givin' it to us?

33:11.690 --> 33:14.193
Why not just give it to one
of your old crews?

33:14.226 --> 33:17.563
You must be Tristan.

33:19.431 --> 33:21.800
Yeah, that's me.

33:21.833 --> 33:24.203
'Cause I like you, Tristan.

33:24.236 --> 33:26.605
I been watchin' you.

33:26.638 --> 33:29.007
You really handle business
very well.

33:30.209 --> 33:32.678
Besides, you owe me.

33:32.711 --> 33:35.381
How you figure that?

33:35.414 --> 33:38.584
You took out one of my crews,
but you didn't bother to get permission.

33:38.617 --> 33:40.686
Now make no mistake.

33:40.719 --> 33:45.691
Now, this is not a demand.
It's a request.

33:45.724 --> 33:48.660
Shit, motherfuckers, I ain't gonna
beg y'all to make this money.

33:48.694 --> 33:53.532
- What is it?
- It's a form of cocaine.

33:53.565 --> 33:57.369
Don't worry, little man.
We can teach you how to cook that up.

33:57.403 --> 34:00.806
What do you call it?
It's called "crack."

34:02.874 --> 34:06.245
And that was the beginning.

34:06.278 --> 34:08.447
♪ Bitch, what is it Cross over ♪

34:11.617 --> 34:14.453
And this, this is the end.

34:14.485 --> 34:17.156
♪ You never seen 'em drop like
this and lock they ass up ♪

34:17.188 --> 34:20.259
♪ Make it hot like this and
still don't spill my drink ♪

34:20.292 --> 34:23.829
♪ My shit real on these streets
Feel my love for concrete ♪♪

34:23.862 --> 34:26.364
Brian Torrance and Archie Tyler.

34:28.234 --> 34:30.335
They were detectives
assigned to our case.

34:30.369 --> 34:33.205
See, after 12 years,
the local cops couldn't catch us,

34:33.239 --> 34:35.407
so the brass assigned
Abbott and Costello here...

34:35.440 --> 34:37.643
to make their presence known,

34:37.676 --> 34:40.879
thinkin' that, if the heat was
on, we'd slow down a little,

34:40.911 --> 34:43.382
maybe make a mistake
so they could catch us.

34:43.415 --> 34:45.817
As usual, they were wrong.

34:45.851 --> 34:49.655
How about it, Tris? Any idea why
somebody'd come in here, rob your uncle?

34:49.688 --> 34:52.424
No, man.

34:52.458 --> 34:56.495
- No idea whatsoever?
- That's what I just said.

34:56.527 --> 34:58.764
Well, why is it that I
don't believe you?

35:00.766 --> 35:03.702
I don't know.

35:03.735 --> 35:06.772
Maybe you just a naturally
suspicious kinda guy.

35:06.805 --> 35:09.241
Let me ask you a question.

35:09.275 --> 35:12.478
Why would they send two vice
detectives to investigate a robbery?

35:12.511 --> 35:15.214
Fourteen-Paul...
Drug-related theft.

35:17.849 --> 35:20.286
And what makes you think
it's drug-related?

35:20.319 --> 35:22.354
I don't know.

35:22.388 --> 35:25.591
Maybe because the owner
is a drug dealer.

35:25.624 --> 35:28.827
Whatever, man.
So, what happened, Tris?

35:28.860 --> 35:31.430
One of your little crackhead
buddies get all mad at ya?

35:31.463 --> 35:36.502
If you two
wasn't so damn pathetic,

35:36.535 --> 35:38.837
you'd almost be funny.

35:38.870 --> 35:41.773
But instead, you're nothin'.

35:43.209 --> 35:45.544
I'm nothin'?

35:45.577 --> 35:47.913
You got no idea
how close we are, fucko!

35:47.946 --> 35:50.449
You and your little crew
are done.

35:50.482 --> 35:52.894
I guess that means you won't be searchin'
too hard for the guy that robbed us.

35:52.918 --> 35:55.454
Now, will you?
Hey, Tris.

35:55.487 --> 35:57.523
If I was you,

35:57.556 --> 35:59.825
the shop would be the last
thing I'd be worried about.

35:59.858 --> 36:03.329
You better start growin' yourself
some eyes in the back of your head.

36:16.575 --> 36:18.610
What the fuck
were they doin' in here?

36:18.644 --> 36:20.812
Hey, I didn't call them.
They just showed up.

36:20.846 --> 36:22.881
Kinda like fungus.

36:22.914 --> 36:24.950
It ain't funny, Unc.

36:24.983 --> 36:27.219
Torrance and Tyler have it in for me.
You know that.

36:27.253 --> 36:28.987
I told you not to talk
to them clowns.

36:29.020 --> 36:31.257
I didn't call them,

36:31.290 --> 36:32.891
and I didn't tell them
anything, Tristan.

36:34.893 --> 36:37.363
Look, I'm not one of them
little punks on the street.

36:37.396 --> 36:41.233
So do me a favor... don't
talk to me like I am.

36:48.374 --> 36:50.376
I'm sorry, Unc.

36:51.543 --> 36:53.579
How much did they get anyway?

36:53.612 --> 36:57.349
Couple hundred dollars
out of the register.

36:57.383 --> 36:59.885
Couldn't open the safe.

36:59.918 --> 37:03.689
Why don't you put bars on the windows and
doors like everybody else on this street?

37:03.722 --> 37:06.392
I've been livin' and workin' in
this neighborhood all my life.

37:06.425 --> 37:09.995
I ain't never had no bars on the window.
I ain't about to start now.

37:10.028 --> 37:13.532
Times change.
You got that right.

37:13.565 --> 37:15.601
Twelve-year-olds
killin' each other.

37:15.634 --> 37:19.271
Goddamn psychopaths
everywhere you look.

37:19.305 --> 37:22.341
Look, I just came by
to make a bank run anyway.

37:22.374 --> 37:24.042
How much we got to deposit?

37:24.075 --> 37:26.412
About four grand.

37:32.318 --> 37:35.421
Cool.
Be safe.

37:35.454 --> 37:37.489
I will.

37:37.523 --> 37:39.758
Hey, look, Unc, um,

37:39.791 --> 37:42.328
I'm sorry I snapped at you earlier.
I didn't mean it.

37:42.361 --> 37:44.396
