We provided you a good home.
You could've been anything you wanted to.

01:12:55.739 --> 01:12:58.174
Why?

01:12:58.207 --> 01:13:00.677
Why do you sell drugs, Tristan?

01:13:00.710 --> 01:13:03.913
How do I tell my father,
like a twig in a tornado,

01:13:03.947 --> 01:13:05.915
I got caught up in this shit...

01:13:05.949 --> 01:13:08.418
That my loyalty to my friends
was like a curse...

01:13:08.452 --> 01:13:11.020
and a blessing at the same time?

01:13:11.054 --> 01:13:13.890
Yet here he is, standing in front of
me, waiting for an answer.

01:13:13.923 --> 01:13:18.061
But I don't have one.
All I can say is:

01:13:18.094 --> 01:13:20.430
'Cause I'm good at it.

01:13:22.632 --> 01:13:24.734
Tell Joanie I'll be by
to see her later.

01:13:33.176 --> 01:13:35.512
So what's up now, yo?

01:13:35.545 --> 01:13:37.847
I'm out.
The price is too high.

01:13:37.881 --> 01:13:39.816
I'm out.

01:13:59.903 --> 01:14:02.071
I hope you like them scrambled.

01:14:02.105 --> 01:14:04.207
♪ Well, well the girl is thick ♪

01:14:04.240 --> 01:14:06.242
♪ Sure look good

01:14:06.275 --> 01:14:08.878
♪ Can't tell I shake
when she come around ♪

01:14:08.912 --> 01:14:11.681
♪♪

01:14:14.050 --> 01:14:16.720
So were you surprised
that I was here?

01:14:16.753 --> 01:14:18.988
I would've been surprised
if you wasn't here.

01:14:19.022 --> 01:14:21.758
God, you are so arrogant.

01:14:21.791 --> 01:14:23.793
Yeah, well, you here, ain't ya?

01:14:29.298 --> 01:14:31.801
So, what about this guy Jack?

01:14:31.835 --> 01:14:33.970
What about him?

01:14:34.003 --> 01:14:36.172
Are you gonna call him?
Maybe.

01:14:36.205 --> 01:14:38.174
What's it gonna hurt
to talk to him?

01:14:38.207 --> 01:14:41.010
Why you campaignin' so hard
for this dude?

01:14:41.044 --> 01:14:43.913
I told you... I get a cut.

01:14:43.947 --> 01:14:46.149
We already got a supplier.

01:14:46.182 --> 01:14:50.053
Maybe you know him. A big-headed,
ugly motherfucker named Benny.

01:14:50.086 --> 01:14:53.022
Who's overcharging you,
and you know it.

01:14:53.056 --> 01:14:57.627
You guys are paying 18 grand a
key when you should be paying 15.

01:14:57.661 --> 01:15:02.666
I think it makes good business
sense to keep all your options open.

01:15:02.699 --> 01:15:06.570
- How you know all this?
- I listen. I hear things.

01:15:06.603 --> 01:15:09.839
You got a sweet thing
with Benny.

01:15:09.873 --> 01:15:12.742
He got your ass set up
with that restaurant and shit.

01:15:12.776 --> 01:15:14.778
Why you tryin' so hard
to get out of it?

01:15:14.811 --> 01:15:17.180
I don't see a dime
from that place.

01:15:17.213 --> 01:15:19.983
I made that place,
and I don't see a dime.

01:15:20.016 --> 01:15:22.786
I don't have anything
but what little bit he gives me,

01:15:22.819 --> 01:15:24.396
and he thinks that'll keep me
comin' around.

01:15:24.420 --> 01:15:28.592
But I ain't lookin' to spend the
rest of my life makin' him rich.

01:15:28.625 --> 01:15:30.960
It ain't good to stay
in one place for too long.

01:15:30.994 --> 01:15:34.564
Sooner or later,
something or somebody catches up with you.

01:15:36.800 --> 01:15:40.303
How do you even know this
Jack motherfucker is a player?

01:15:40.336 --> 01:15:43.139
What if he's a cop?

01:15:43.172 --> 01:15:46.275
I been around enough players in the
game to know a cop when I see one.

01:15:46.309 --> 01:15:49.245
And he ain't no cop.

01:15:49.278 --> 01:15:52.081
But if you're so worried,
why don't you have him checked out?

01:15:52.115 --> 01:15:56.219
And if he does check out,
you willin' to go up against Benny?

01:15:56.252 --> 01:16:00.556
After what we just did,
you got the nerve to ask me that?

01:16:03.693 --> 01:16:05.629
You got a point there.

01:16:11.034 --> 01:16:13.603
Excuse me.
Mrs. Mackey?

01:16:14.838 --> 01:16:16.572
Can we ask you a few questions?

01:16:18.975 --> 01:16:21.310
I'm afraid I can't talk right now.
I'm very busy.

01:16:21.344 --> 01:16:24.147
That's not what you
said before, Martine.

01:16:24.180 --> 01:16:26.149
I never should have helped you.

01:16:26.182 --> 01:16:30.119
Hey, maybe that's the smartest thing
you ever did. What do you want?

01:16:30.153 --> 01:16:34.090
We just wanna help you help Tristan.
He's in a lot of trouble.

01:16:34.123 --> 01:16:36.660
The only chance he has of
gettin' out of it alive is us.

01:16:36.693 --> 01:16:39.896
You don't wanna
see him dead, right?

01:16:39.929 --> 01:16:41.831
So we need
a little more information.

01:16:47.771 --> 01:16:51.007
Look, you've gotten all the
information you're gonna get from me.

01:16:51.040 --> 01:16:53.719
'Cause you don't wanna help Tristan.
You only wanna help yourselves.

01:16:53.743 --> 01:16:55.712
Excuse me.

01:16:55.745 --> 01:16:57.847
Don't be stupid, Martine.

01:17:00.216 --> 01:17:02.652
Dead is a long time.

01:17:03.419 --> 01:17:05.655
Fuck off.

01:17:08.958 --> 01:17:10.894
Yeah, man.

01:17:24.373 --> 01:17:26.943
Hi.

01:17:26.976 --> 01:17:29.012
Hi there.

01:17:30.980 --> 01:17:33.082
Where were you?

01:17:33.116 --> 01:17:35.819
I went to the Vineyard.
Didn't you get my note?

01:17:37.954 --> 01:17:40.256
What note?

01:17:49.365 --> 01:17:51.334
This note?

01:17:51.367 --> 01:17:54.403
"Dear Tristan,

01:17:54.437 --> 01:17:58.407
"I went to have the chain you gave
me fixed because it was broken.

01:17:58.441 --> 01:18:01.110
"I know this little place in Oak
Bluffs that will do a good job.

01:18:03.512 --> 01:18:07.817
"Thinkin' about us,
the chain reminds me how much I love you.

01:18:07.851 --> 01:18:10.219
"You do what you have to do
for us and for yourself,

01:18:10.253 --> 01:18:12.221
"just as you've always done,

01:18:12.255 --> 01:18:14.223
"and I'll be here
for better or for worse.

01:18:14.257 --> 01:18:17.393
No questions asked.
Martine."

01:18:27.070 --> 01:18:29.305
It looks nice.

01:18:31.440 --> 01:18:33.376
I love you, Tristan.

01:18:44.487 --> 01:18:46.489
You'd never keep anything
from me, Martine, right?

01:18:46.522 --> 01:18:48.491
Anything important,
I mean, right?

01:18:48.524 --> 01:18:50.994
Right.

01:18:51.027 --> 01:18:53.729
Why would you ask me that?

01:18:55.031 --> 01:18:57.433
Because trust is everything.

01:18:57.466 --> 01:19:01.037
Without it, you have nothing.
Do you agree?

01:19:03.106 --> 01:19:05.274
Yeah.

01:19:05.308 --> 01:19:08.177
Then what the fuck were
them cops doin' here then?

01:19:08.211 --> 01:19:09.979
They were here for you, Tristan.
Why?

01:19:10.013 --> 01:19:11.948
I don't know why.

01:19:13.549 --> 01:19:15.518
I don't know.
They didn't say.

01:19:15.551 --> 01:19:17.787
That's it? They didn't
say nothin' else?

01:19:17.821 --> 01:19:20.289
That's it.
They didn't say nothin' else.

01:19:34.003 --> 01:19:35.538
Look, Tristan, um...

01:19:37.974 --> 01:19:40.977
I don't feel well.
I'm just gonna go lie down, okay?

01:19:41.010 --> 01:19:42.812
It's probably the baby
or somethin'.

01:19:45.514 --> 01:19:48.384
Yeah, you should do that.

01:20:01.530 --> 01:20:05.134
Shit.

01:20:13.609 --> 01:20:15.344
Fuck.

01:20:24.287 --> 01:20:26.455
Who is it?

01:20:26.489 --> 01:20:28.524
It's me, young pimp.
I need to rap to ya.

01:20:30.994 --> 01:20:33.429
Twinkie?
Yeah.

01:20:42.305 --> 01:20:45.174
You know
what fuckin' time it is?

01:20:45.208 --> 01:20:47.944
It's about 4:00 a.m.

01:20:47.977 --> 01:20:50.113
What you doin' here, man?

01:20:50.146 --> 01:20:52.548
Like I said,
I came to rap to ya.

01:20:52.581 --> 01:20:55.384
You don't know me, motherfucker.

01:20:55.418 --> 01:20:57.954
Don't ever just show up
at my fuckin' crib.

01:20:57.987 --> 01:21:00.132
Let me know when you're through
actin' like a little bitch.

01:21:00.156 --> 01:21:03.592
What'd you say?

01:21:03.626 --> 01:21:07.630
Look, I know you don't think I came
over here for my motherfuckin' health.

01:21:07.663 --> 01:21:10.934
I got business with you, boy,
and the sooner you stop fuckin' around,

01:21:10.967 --> 01:21:14.503
we can get to it and I
can be on my fuckin' way.

01:21:22.979 --> 01:21:25.459
You got three seconds to say what
the hell it is you gonna say.

01:21:26.315 --> 01:21:28.484
Not in the hallway.

01:21:28.517 --> 01:21:30.553
Five minutes inside,
then I'm out.

01:21:37.093 --> 01:21:39.028
Come on in.

01:21:49.538 --> 01:21:52.575
Can I get a drink?

01:21:54.577 --> 01:21:58.114
Say what the fuck you gonna say,
man, and get the hell outta here.

01:21:58.147 --> 01:22:00.349
Can I at least sit down?

01:22:00.383 --> 01:22:02.185
Sit down, motherfucker.
Damn!

01:22:16.665 --> 01:22:20.970
Look, this ain't no easy thing to
say, so I'm just gonna say it.

01:22:21.004 --> 01:22:23.973
Your mother used to be a ho.

01:22:24.007 --> 01:22:25.941
She worked for me
until just after you was born.

01:22:30.013 --> 01:22:32.348
Is that what you came here
to tell me?

01:22:34.283 --> 01:22:36.219
You don't seem surprised.

01:22:36.252 --> 01:22:39.455
I ain't no kid, motherfucker.

01:22:39.488 --> 01:22:42.191
I been around a long time,

01:22:42.225 --> 01:22:44.193
seen a lot of shit.

01:22:46.429 --> 01:22:48.589
You gonna have to come better
than that to surprise me.

01:22:51.534 --> 01:22:54.270
She ever tell you
about your father?

01:22:54.303 --> 01:22:57.373
She said he was a salesman or
some shit out on the coast.

01:23:00.076 --> 01:23:02.111
She lied, man.

01:23:02.145 --> 01:23:03.679
I'm your father.

01:23:13.722 --> 01:23:17.326
There you go with that bullshit again.
You need to shut the fuck up.

01:23:17.360 --> 01:23:20.629
Man, why would I say some shit
like that if it wasn't true?

01:23:20.663 --> 01:23:23.566
Well, if she was a ho
like you say she was,

01:23:23.599 --> 01:23:25.534
how the fuck you know
who my father is?

01:23:40.316 --> 01:23:43.018
When she got pregnant,
Violet decided to quit hoin'.

01:23:44.587 --> 01:23:47.223
She was in love with me,
and she thought we was a family.

01:23:48.557 --> 01:23:51.160
She was one of
my best girls, man.

01:23:52.561 --> 01:23:55.064
I just wanted to prove to her
you wasn't mine,

01:23:55.098 --> 01:23:58.667
convince her to give you up for adoption
so she and I could keep rollin', you know.

01:23:58.701 --> 01:24:02.271
She swore up and down
you was mine,

01:24:02.305 --> 01:24:04.707
and damn if she wasn't right.

01:24:07.143 --> 01:24:09.712
It's true, man.
I ain't lyin'.

01:24:09.745 --> 01:24:12.381
So why you tellin' me
this shit now?

01:24:16.319 --> 01:24:19.255
'Cause I made another promise...

01:24:19.288 --> 01:24:21.257
to myself...

01:24:21.290 --> 01:24:23.259
that,

01:24:23.292 --> 01:24:26.095
before one of us... died,

01:24:27.296 --> 01:24:29.265
we'd both know the truth.

01:24:38.807 --> 01:24:40.543
You sick, man?

01:24:42.678 --> 01:24:44.647
Can you just get me
a glass of water?

01:24:55.391 --> 01:24:57.326
Twinkie.

01:25:02.765 --> 01:25:05.601
Why didn't you just kill Benny
when you had the chance, man?

01:25:05.634 --> 01:25:07.470
What?

01:25:07.503 --> 01:25:10.639
You and your friends...
You got too large.

01:25:10.673 --> 01:25:12.641
You made him nervous.

01:25:12.675 --> 01:25:14.643
Then you gave him an excuse.

01:25:14.677 --> 01:25:17.780
What the fuck
you talkin' about, man?

01:25:17.813 --> 01:25:20.549
Blue Hill Ave, man.
We closed that place down.

01:25:20.583 --> 01:25:23.252
We're not doin' business
out of there anymore.

01:25:23.286 --> 01:25:24.853
Well, one of you still is.

01:25:24.887 --> 01:25:27.923
Look, Simon,

01:25:27.956 --> 01:25:30.259
he's got me, man.

01:25:31.327 --> 01:25:33.262
I got to do this.

01:25:42.971 --> 01:25:44.940
I got homeys...

01:25:44.973 --> 01:25:47.376
that'll hunt you down
till you drop.

01:25:49.478 --> 01:25:51.647
They gonna be dead
soon after you.

01:26:30.686 --> 01:26:32.421
Forgive me, son.

01:26:55.811 --> 01:26:58.013
Simon was my best friend.

01:26:58.046 --> 01:27:00.015
It was all startin'
to fall apart.

01:27:00.048 --> 01:27:03.519
He was gone, and the only thing
I could do for him now was pray...

01:27:03.552 --> 01:27:05.654
"Ashes to ashes, dust to dust."

01:27:33.716 --> 01:27:37.286
Miss Davis,
I don't know what to say.

01:27:37.320 --> 01:27:39.622
I'm real sorry.

01:27:39.655 --> 01:27:44.026
I thought everything was gonna be okay
now that Thomas was back in his life.

01:27:44.059 --> 01:27:46.929
Thomas?
You knew him better as Twinkie.

01:27:48.797 --> 01:27:51.434
Well, what's Twinkie doin'
in Simon's life?

01:27:51.467 --> 01:27:53.569
He's his father.

01:27:56.672 --> 01:27:59.642
Now, you'd think
he'd care enough...

01:27:59.675 --> 01:28:02.711
to show up for his own son's...

01:28:06.882 --> 01:28:10.353
Why weren't you there
for my boy, Tristan?

01:28:10.386 --> 01:28:13.288
He would've been there for you.

01:28:14.890 --> 01:28:16.825
Let me go!

01:28:36.412 --> 01:28:38.347
You all right, man?

01:28:41.417 --> 01:28:43.352
No.

01:28:46.088 --> 01:28:47.856
What's the word?

01:28:49.124 --> 01:28:52.495
Simon's soldiers
are fightin' for power.

01:28:52.528 --> 01:28:55.964
They ain't gonna be no good
to us if we war with Benny.

01:28:55.998 --> 01:28:58.401
And without Simon,
my people won't budge.

01:28:58.434 --> 01:29:02.137
Hell, I can't even get the motherfuckers
to return a page, never mind combat.

01:29:02.170 --> 01:29:05.040
Everybody knows Benny killed Simon.
Maybe he didn't pull the trigger.

01:29:05.073 --> 01:29:07.843
But they figure that we ain't
got a chance now.

01:29:07.876 --> 01:29:10.813
So, they don't wanna be
around when he comes after us.

01:29:13.015 --> 01:29:16.919
Ain't nobody talkin' about
who d pull the trigger? Nah.

01:29:16.952 --> 01:29:18.921
But Buzz said
when they found him,

01:29:18.954 --> 01:29:21.424
there was "T-W" written
in blood on the floor.

01:29:21.457 --> 01:29:24.493
But that can mean anything. We gotta
figure out what the fuck we gonna do.

01:29:30.566 --> 01:29:32.935
That ain't got nothin'
to do with me.

01:29:32.968 --> 01:29:35.037
Come on now, T.

01:29:35.070 --> 01:29:36.910
So, what, you just gonna
leave us hangin', man?

01:29:41.710 --> 01:29:43.679
Did you say "T-W"?

01:29:43.712 --> 01:29:46.014
Yeah, man, but that
could mean anything!

01:29:50.653 --> 01:29:54.757
Simon!
My baby.

01:29:54.790 --> 01:29:59.127
God.

01:29:59.161 --> 01:30:01.730
What?

01:30:01.764 --> 01:30:05.668
- I know who did it.
- Who?

01:30:05.701 --> 01:30:08.637
I'll tell you on the way.
Come on. Let's go.

01:30:13.709 --> 01:30:15.878
Martine.

01:30:17.179 --> 01:30:19.848
I gotta go.
I got somethin' I gotta do.

01:30:21.183 --> 01:30:23.686
You're gonna go after him,
aren't you?

01:30:26.822 --> 01:30:28.791
Look, I don't want you
to go back to the house.

01:30:28.824 --> 01:30:31.126
Take the car and go to
your father's house. Why?

01:30:31.159 --> 01:30:32.928
'Cause ain't nobody
gonna find you in Malden.

01:30:32.961 --> 01:30:34.897
Tristan...

01:30:37.766 --> 01:30:39.702
Okay.

01:30:41.504 --> 01:30:44.473
- Is he here for you?
- No, Tristan.

01:30:44.507 --> 01:30:47.810
- Why would you even think that?
- Stop the game! I know it was you.

01:30:47.843 --> 01:30:51.680
You broke my heart.
Tristan, he said he wanted to help you.

01:30:51.714 --> 01:30:54.750
- And you believed him?
- Yes! I wanted to believe him!

01:30:54.783 --> 01:30:58.020
Because I wanted you out of this so bad!
So I thought I was helping.

01:30:58.053 --> 01:31:00.198
That's how you help?
Help him put a bug in Simon's car?

01:31:00.222 --> 01:31:03.125
What? No, I wouldn't do that.

01:31:03.158 --> 01:31:05.894
I wouldn't do that. I wouldn't
help him do something like that!

01:31:05.928 --> 01:31:08.230
- Ain't no sense in lyin' now.
- I'm not lying, Tristan!

01:31:08.263 --> 01:31:10.633
I didn't do that.

01:31:10.666 --> 01:31:13.168
I told them when Rob's barbershop
got broken into. That's it.

01:31:13.201 --> 01:31:15.137
What?

01:31:15.170 --> 01:31:18.607
Torrance and Tyler
came up to me a while ago,

01:31:18.641 --> 01:31:20.909
and they asked me if I wanted
to tell them anything.

01:31:20.943 --> 01:31:23.579
If there's anything that I had
to tell them, to give 'em a call.

01:31:23.612 --> 01:31:26.057
But I didn't tell you because I
know how you feel about the police.

01:31:26.081 --> 01:31:28.617
But, for some reason,
I thought that they could help me.

01:31:28.651 --> 01:31:30.719
So, when Rob's barbershop
got broken into,

01:31:30.753 --> 01:31:32.921
I gave Torrance and Tyler
a call.

01:31:32.955 --> 01:31:36.659
They came down. I thought that they
could help, but they didn't help.

01:31:36.692 --> 01:31:38.794
And all they did was,
was harass you that day.

01:31:38.827 --> 01:31:41.730
And I thought that...

01:31:41.764 --> 01:31:44.166
All they did was use me
to try and get to you.

01:31:44.199 --> 01:31:47.135
But I swear to God, that's all I told 'em.
I didn't say anything else.

01:31:47.169 --> 01:31:49.872
I swear.
All right. All right.

01:31:51.907 --> 01:31:54.209
- I believe you.
- That's all I did.

01:31:54.242 --> 01:31:56.278
I wouldn't set Simon up.
I wouldn't do that.

01:31:56.311 --> 01:31:58.814
All right. All right.
I swear it.

01:32:00.015 --> 01:32:02.585
I'm so sorry.
I believe you.

01:32:05.287 --> 01:32:07.690
I gotta go.
No, I gotta go.

01:32:07.723 --> 01:32:09.592
No questions asked,
remember? Come on.

01:32:09.625 --> 01:32:11.760
Come on now.
Come on.

01:32:11.794 --> 01:32:13.528
No questions asked.

01:32:15.297 --> 01:32:18.033
I'll see you later
at your father's house.

01:32:18.066 --> 01:32:20.002
I promise.

01:32:36.018 --> 01:32:37.920
A'ight. So who did it, man?

01:32:37.953 --> 01:32:40.723
Twinkie.

01:32:40.756 --> 01:32:42.925
Twinkie?

01:32:42.958 --> 01:32:45.828
Why in the fuck would
Twinkie wanna kill Simon?

01:32:45.861 --> 01:32:48.230
Benny sent him.

01:32:48.263 --> 01:32:50.766
He knew Twinkie could
get close to him.

01:32:50.799 --> 01:32:52.334
How in the hell he know that?

01:32:54.703 --> 01:32:56.639
Twinkie was Simon's father.

